Fixed #234 Clicking month bar shows report that's off by one month

Fix issue #234 Off-by-one in month report title

When I click the month of December 2012, the title of my report view is
January 2013. When I click the final month (currently January 2013), the
title is correct. The result is that the final two months in report view
have the same title.

Fix Promo Downloads when compiling with Xcode 4.2

PromoCodeOperation initWithProduct:numberOfCodes: initialized __block NSInteger numberOfCodesToRequest with a random minus value when compiling with LLVM GCC 4.2. Switching to LLVM 3.0 solved the issue.

Add option to group Day and Week data by Apple Fiscal Calendar

Dates based on Apple's fiscal calendar available here:
https://itunesconnect.apple.com/WebObjects/iTunesConnect.woa/wo/3.0.0.9.7.3.1.5

They'll have to be updated manually as Apple publishes each fiscal year.
Their fiscal calendar only has 364 days in a year, so at some point
they'll probably add an extra week somewhere to catch up.

Fix what looks like a daylight savings time issue with date comparisons.
When comparing the dates of the filename to the loaded date.  When the
date was saved to the data file it seems to have included a time of
1am.  The date was subsequently compared to ldate which had a time of
12am so some files were not loaded properly.
